g.aria-label: Estimated environmental impacts of grass-fed beef, relative to feedlot beef, per kilogram of beef. Data on greenhouse gases, the higher fossil fuel estimate, number of cattle, manure, nitrogen pollution, andphosphorus excretions are given byCapper. Lupo et al.provides the lower estimates of greenhousegas emissions.Tichenor et al.estimate land use, the lower fossil fuel energy value, water,eutrophication, and acidification.Capper, J. "Is the Grass Always Greener? Comparing the Environmental Impact of Conventional, Natural and Grass-Fed BeefProduction Systems". Animals2, pp. 127-143.Lupo, C., Clay, D., Benning, J., Stone, J. "Life-cycle assessment of the beef cattle production system for the northern greatplains, USA". Journal of Environmental Quality42(5), pp. 1386-94.September 2013.Tichenor, N., Peters, C., Norris, G., Thoma, G., Griffin, T."Life cycle environmental consequences of grass-fed and dairy beefproduction systems in the Northeastern United States". Journal of Cleaner Production142(4), pp. 1619-1628.January 2017.
